      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It hurts to feel devalued just because of the pressure to be constantly connected to a demanding system. The feeling of being replaceable as \"extra noise\" is exhausting, but try to visualize breaking that cycle by turning off screens or resting to reclaim a sense of self. You deserve to feel your worth without needing to validate yourself through endless digital clicks or tasks that can be done at a slower pace. If this disconnection feels overwhelming, a grief counselor or suicide prevention helpline can offer support when things feel this bleak. Please consider reaching out if you fear hurting yourself or ending things to make this pain stop.",
